{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, the I-graded local system V 0 globally splits as",
    "where V 0 ⟨q⟩ is a ⟨q⟩-graded local system and V 0 ⟨q⟩ ̸ = 0 if and only if ⟨q⟩ is an active circle.",
    "A local system V 0 → ∂ graded by a single Stokes circle ⟨q⟩, here with ramification order r = 3.",
    "For any direction d ∈ ∂, the fibre ⟨q⟩ d = π -1 (d) = {k 0,.",
    ", k r-1 } contains r points, and we have a locally constant decomposition"
  ]
}